Released my PA for a day to allow her and her daughter (who recently had Work Experience in the my Lab) to attend to represent FBS and enthuse show-goers about FBS in particular, and biology in general
The event was aimed at schoolchildren, to enthuse and inform them about biology and encourage them to choose it as a school subject, University subject and career choice. We had a stand with several interactive activities aimed at children of various ages and abilities such as making a model of an axon, mirror-writing, looking at a skeleton and discussing its form in relation to its function, various exercise-related activities, and the opportunity to handle an artificial hip joint.
My PA's daughter surprised herself at how well she did with this, and she is halfway through her BSc in Biological Sciences at Birmingham.
